\f0\b \cf2 \strokec2 Description//Functionality\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf2 A task manager file allows a user to\
	-Login (prompted to enter a username and password)\
	-Register a user with a new username and password\
	-Add a new task, including details such as the assigned user, title, description and due date\
	-View all tasks listed in the tasks.txt file, and select a task in order to mark it as complete or edit the assigned user or due date\
	-View all tasks assigned to themselves\
	-Generate reports through generating two files:\
		-task_overview.txt\
			This contains the total number of generate and tracked tasks, total number of completed/uncompleted/overdue tasks, as well as the % of tasks incomplete and/or overdue\
		-user_overview.txt\
			This file generates a report concerning the total number of registered users, total number of tasks and statistics regarding the number of (completed/Incompleted/overdue) tasks assigned to that user\
	-Display statistics\
		This reads the above files and displays reports on the screen in a user-friendly manner. If these text files do not exist then it calls the code to generate them\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480\partightenfactor0

