\f0\b \cf2 \strokec2 Installation\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf4 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 Install all files into the same folder and run the task_manager.py file on any Python interpreter. The system requires user input in the terminal\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 Files\
1 - tasks.txt stores a list of all the tasks the team is working on. The data for each task is stored  on a separate line in the text file. Each line includes the following data:\
	-The username of the person to whom the task is assigned\
	-The task title\
	-A description of the task\
	-The due date that the task was assigned to the user\
	-The due date for the task\
	-Either a \'91Yes\'92 or \'91No\'92 value that specifies if the task has been completed yet\
\
2 - user.txt stores the username and password for each user that has permission to use the program\cf4 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf4 Usage
\f2\b0\fs24 \cf4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 When the program is run, the user is requested to login. For assistance, the user.txt file stores the login details of current registered users. The main menu then appears and the user is requested to enter details in the terminal.\
\
Note that only the admin has permission to register new users.\

